<HEADLINE> Ullrich Wins Fourth Stage of Switzerland Cycle Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Jan Ullrich of the
Telekom team won the 183-kilometer fourth stage of the Tour of
Switzerland cycle race in Kandersteg on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Ullrich finished 38 seconds ahead of Italy's Stefano Garzelli
and Roland Meier of Switzerland in this stretch between la
Chaux-de-Fonds and Kandersteg.
</P>
<P>
France's Christophe Agnolutto, who crossed the line more than
three minutes behind Ullrich, retained the leader's yellow
jersey. 
</P>
