<HEADLINE> Primary Health Care Foundation of China Founded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Primary Health Care Foundation of
China, aimed at promoting basic health care services in China's
poor regions, was established today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Established by the Chinese Peasants and Workers Democratic
Party (CPWDP), the organization is under the administration of the
Ministry of Health (MOH).
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the foundation is to raise funds for the people
in poor areas for their need of medical care, said the
organization's chairman Lu Jiaxi, who is also vice-chairman of the
Standing Committee of National People's Congress (NPC) and
chairman of the Central Committee of CPWDP.
</P>
<P>
The foundation was set up in line with the government's goal to
provide health care to the entire nation and to completely wipe
out poverty by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
State Councillor Peng Peiyun congratulated the formation of the
foundation at its opening ceremony, saying it will play an active
role in aiding the poor and sharing the government's
responsibilities in the effort. She emphasized that the
organization will have full government support.
</P>
<P>
Wang Guangying and Wu Jieping, both vice-chairmen of NPC
Standing Committee, together with Chen Minzhang, minister of MOH,
attended today's ceremony.  
</P>
</TEXT>
