<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan and England Score Big Wins in World Youth Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 20 (Xinhua) -- England whitewashed the
United Arab Emirates 5-0 on Friday to sail into the last 16 at the
world youth soccer championships with one game to play.
</P>
<P>
It joined defending champions Argentina, Mexico and Spain in
the knock-out round of the 24-nation under-20 tournament.
</P>
<P>
Daniel Murphy scored a hat-trick, two in the first half and one
in the second, as England won the group F game at Johor Baru.
</P>
<P>
Michael Owen scored the fourth in the 51st before UAE's
subsitute goalkeeper Ali Yarees netted an own-goal eight minutes
later.
</P>
<P>
England surged to the top of the group with six points after
main rivals Mexico were held to a surprising 1-1 draw by Cote
d'Ivoire in another group F game Friday.
</P>
<P>
In group E at Kangar, Argentina survived a scare before downing
spirited Canada 2-1 through a 65th minute penalty converted by
Roman Riquelme.
</P>
<P>
Bernardo Romeo gave Argentina the lead in the 32nd minute, but
Jason Bent levelled the score a minute before half-time as Canada
thwarted their fancied rivals during a fast-paced encounter.
</P>
<P>
Also in the group, Australia edged Hungary 1-0 on a last-minute
header goal from subsitute Daniel Allsopp, who came in the 82nd
min.
</P>
<P>
At four points, Australia is now two points behind Argentina
who won two games.
</P>
<P>
In another lopsided game, Japan drubbed Costa Rica 6-2 in Group
D at Kuantan, scoring thrice in each half.
</P>
<P>
Japan, with three points from two matches, now needs a draw in
their last group game against Paraguay on Monday to move up from
the group.
</P>
<P>
Spain maintained their unbeaten run in the same group with a
2-1 win over Paraguay, who were left with a solitary point.
</P>
<P>
The top two teams in each of the six groups and four best
third-placers move into the knock-out rounds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
