<HEADLINE> Mandela Urges to Solve Refugee Problem in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 20 (Xinhua) -- South African President Nelson
Mandela has called for serious commitment to solve the refugee
problem in Africa.
</P>
<P>
In a message to mark Africa Refugee Day today, Mandela described
the refugee problem as a serious threat to regional and continental
peace and security.
</P>
<P>
The refugee crisis, involving at least six million people, cannot
be treated in isolation from the economic, political and social causes
which give rise to it, he said.
</P>
<P>
Mandela said finding solution to the crisis is closely linked to
achieving peace, upholding the rule of law, democracy and a human
rights culture.
</P>
<P>
Mandela, also the current chairman of the 12-nation Southern
African Development Community, attributes the fact that Southern
Africa stopped to be a major refugee-producing region a few yeas ago
to political settlements and smooth democratic transitions that have
taken place in the region.
</P>
<P>
The South African leaders say an integrated approach is required
to tackle the diverse issues confronting Africa and the rest of the
world today. enditem

