<HEADLINE> CITES, UNEP Signs Memorandum of Understanding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 20 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Environment
Program (UNEP) signed here today a memorandum of understanding with
the Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species (CITES)
to enhance the cooperation between the two world bodies.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, UNEP would be expected to assist the CITES
Secretariat to ensure that it meets the growing tasks assigned to it by
the international convention on endangered species.
</P>
<P>
The implementation of the CITES objectives in Africa would be
among some of the major functions of UNEP.
</P>
<P>
UNEP Deputy Executive Director Rueben Olembo said the CITES could
not afford to ignore members of the civil society as they were the
ones who implemented and benefited from decisions. enditem

