<HEADLINE> Cyprus Launches Anti-Drugs War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 20 (Xinhua) -- The Cypriot government has
launched a campaign against drugs to counter a rise in drug abuse
among young Cypriots.
</P>
<P>
"The Cypriot government, recognizing the seriousness of the
drug problem, having assessed all social, psychological, economic
and cultural factors involved in drug use and having studied all
international declarations and agreements, decided to adopt a
national policy against drugs," Health Minister Christos Solomis
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Solomis made the remark at a press conference to mark the
International Day Against Drugs that falls on June 26.
</P>
<P>
The health minister noted the rise in drug abuse is most
prevalent in people between the ages of 16 and 35, while new
drug substances have found their way to the island of Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
However, Solomis stressed that drug addiction cases in Cyprus
are at what he called an enviable level in comparison with that
in Europe.
</P>
<P>
Only four deaths were reported so far in Cyprus as a result of
the drug abuse.
</P>
<P>
According to the Minister, the national drug policy includes
the foundation and operation of an anti-drug policy center, the
establishment of special training programs, therapy and
rehabilitation of drug addicts and financial support for the
drug policy from the public and private sectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
