<HEADLINE> Greek Army Take Delivery of French Armoured Vehicles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 20 (Xinhua) -- The Greek army today took delivery
of six French-made armored vehicles.
</P>
<P>
The "pan hard VBL" is reportedly a three-ton 4x4 vehicle which
can travel in water at 1.5 meters per second and reach speeds of
up to 100 kph on land.
</P>
<P>
With a fuel tank enabling it to cover a distance of 600
kilometers on one fill-up, the vehicle, with a three-men crew, is
armed with "Milan" anti-tank missiles and a 7.62 mm machine gun.
</P>
<P>
The vehicles will be used by the Greek troops participating in
the Italian-led multinational protection force in Albania.
</P>
