<TEXT>
<P>
DENVER, Colorado, June 20 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill
Clinton and Russian President Boris Yeltsin are to meet here today
hours before the summit of leading industrialized nations opens.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders will discuss European security issues, arms
control and Russia's integration into the global economy. The
meeting will be the third between them this year.
</P>
<P>
Clinton and Yeltsin would continue their dialogue on the
expansion of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) and the
implementation of START 2 nuclear reduction agreement.
</P>
