<HEADLINE> Romanian Leader Vows to Press for NATO Entry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Prime Minister Victor
Ciorbea said today his country will keep on pressing for the entry
into NATO until a summit next month in Madrid.
</P>
<P>
"We will try to act until the time of the Madrid meeting to
have a very wise decision taken there. This is our duty toward our
own people and toward those who support us," he told reporters
before his meeting with U.S. Defense Secretary William Cohen.
</P>
