Hungary and the Czech Republic to become the new members in the
first round of invitation to the alliance.
</P>
<P>
"We have been saddened by the (U.S.) decision," Ciorbea said.
"At the same time, obviously we are very interested to develop a
strategic partnership between our two countries."
</P>
<P>
Cohen indicated that the United States did not say "no" to
Romania's entry into NATO last week, just said "not yet." He said
he must make it "perfectly clear." 
</P>
