<HEADLINE> Nigeria Begins Survey on Number of Languages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 20 (Xinhua) -- A survey to ascertain the actual
number of languages in Nigeria has been kicked off in a bid to
facilitate their development, the Nigerian Educational Research
and Development Council (NERDC) said today.
</P>
<P>
The number of languages in the country is currently put at 250
and 300, but it might be incorrect, according to NERDC Executive
Secretary Uduogie Ivowi.
</P>
<P>
As part of efforts to make the speaking and writing of the
languages easy, the council has developed orthographies for 42
Nigerian languages and published manuals on them.
</P>
<P>
"We are doing orthographies for another set of six languages,"
Ivowi said, quoted by the News Agency of Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
According to him, NERDC has established a data base of
Nigerian languages and dialects with information on the
population of speakers and users as well as their geographic
spread.
</P>
<P>
The scholar is in favor of teaching school children in the
mother tongue, saying that it would spur better comprehension and
understanding, especially of technology comprehension.  
</P>
</TEXT>
