<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus' House of Representatives
President Spyros Kyprianou has expressed reservations about the
the forthcoming U.N.-sponsored direct talks between leaders of the
Greek and Turkish communities in Cyprus, Cyprus News Agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Kyprianou was quoted as saying that it is unrealistic to expect
Turkey to abandon its "expansionist policy" in Cyprus with "simple
advices."
</P>
<P>
