<P>
"I am a little excited, thinking about the visit to Beijing,"
Nemtsov said, "because it is my first visit to China. I knew long
ago that Chinese people are brave, industrious and honest."
</P>
<P>
During the visit of the Russian Premier to China, according to
Nemtsov, he is expected to sign with Chinese officials a package
of agreements, concerning, among others, energy, electric power,
traffic and trade.
</P>
<P>
Nemtrov believed that the projects, such as extracting and
providing for China national gas from Irkutsk region and oil from
East Siberia, as well as building a national gas pipeline passed
through Mongolia and China to East Asia, have a great significance
to economic development for both countries and the East Asian
region.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Russia and China should actively enlarge their
exchanging fields of industry and investment.
</P>
<P>
Some leaders, bankers and bosses of large companies from the
Russian border areas will also go to Beijing with him, Nemtsov
said.
</P>
<P>
Nemtsov said that Russia exceeds other countries in economic
cooperation with China, for the two countries have more than 4,000
kilometres of common border, and there are plentiful resources in
the Far East area of Russia, and the two countries have
traditional relations of friendship.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the Russian "East policy", Nemtrov said that
Russia sees the world as a multipolar and denies the right of some
big powers to govern the world. It is equally important for Russia
to cooperate with East, West and South, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
