<HEADLINE> Deals Worth 3.4 Billion US Dollars Struck in Harbin Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The 8th Harbin Economic and Trade
Fair in Harbin, capital city of northeast China's Heilongjiang
Province, which ended today after a seven-day run, has landed
deals worth 3.4 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
More than 6,000 business people from more than 50 countries and
regions attended the event. Foreign trade companies occupied one
eighth of the exhibition stands.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that contracted deals were down 20 percent from
last year, standing at 1.72 billion US dollars, and the ratio of
barter trade dropped by 34 percent from 1996.
</P>
<P>
The number of major companies from Japan, the Republic of
Korea, Thailand and Taiwan region which came to the fair, as well
as those from Russia and other states of the Commonwealth of
Independent States, have increased dramatically.
</P>
<P>
The Harbin Economic and Trade Fair, one of the major four trade
fairs in China, has witnessed more than 30 billion yuan in deals
since its inauguration in 1990.  
</P>
</TEXT>
