<HEADLINE> Dhaka Stock Market Ends Week Dull </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Without showing any positive
reaction to the national budget announced on June 12, the Dhaka
Stock Exchange (DSE) last week witnessed a downtrend in share
trading, except on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Owing to fund shortage, all the key indices declined during the
week from their previous week's positions. The DSE share price
index declined by 39.14 points to close at 1189.29 Thursday
against 1157.43 on the last trading day of the previous week.
</P>
<P>
Because of the fund constraints, share trading on the DSE floor
was lackluster over the whole of last week.
</P>
<P>
With June 30 known as "June final" round the corner, investors
were getting ready to make payment against their bank loans with a
view to keeping their goodwill with the banks.
</P>
<P>
During this period, the budget announcement had no influence on
the share market in the absence of any new incentives for share
investors.
</P>
<P>
The market capitalization of the week registered a fall of 2.52
billion taka (about 57.9 million U.S. dollars), ending at 93.53
billion taka (about 2.15 billion dollars) on the last weekend.
</P>
<P>
During the week, the number of total issues traded also
declined to 649 from the previous week's 698.  
</P>
</TEXT>
