<HEADLINE> Novotna Enters Semis at Eastbourne Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Jana Novotna of Czech Republic beat
unseeded Japanese Ai Sugiyama in a rain-interrupted match to sail
into the semi-finals of a women's grasscourt tournament in
Eastbourne on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, defending champion Monica Seles of the United States
lost to Brenda Schultz-McCarthy of the Netherlands 7-5, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Novotna had led the match 6-2, 6-5 and 15-15 to be just three
points away from victory when rain interrupted the play on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The second seed had difficulties to finish off the match on
Saturday, when the strong winds swept past Devonshire Park on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
She needed 46 minutes more and three matchpoints before winning
through 6-2, 6-7, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
In the semi-finals later on Saturday, Novotna will meet
unseeded Natasha Zvereva of Belarus, who disposed of Frenchwoman
Nathalie Tauziat of France 6-4, 5-7, 6-4, in another quarter-final
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Seles, who was trailing by one set to Brenda
Schultz-McCarthy of the Netherlands in a quarter-final delayed
from Thursday, could not reverse her bad luck to lose 7-5, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Eighth-seeded Shultz-McCarthy now faces the winner of the match
between fourth seed Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of Spain and Romanian
Irina Spirlea in the other quarter-final. 
