<HEADLINE> Sino-US Joint Venture to Get Land-Use Right </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai General Motors
Company, the largest Sino-US joint venture in China, has recently
been given land-use rights for 540,000 sq m of land in the Pudong
New Area in Shanghai for building its factory.
</P>
<P>
The 1.5 billion US dollar-company is a joint effort between
Shanghai Automobiles Industry Corp. and the US's General Motors
Corp. (GM).
</P>
<P>
Scheduled to go into operation at the end of the next year, the
new car company is to have an annual production capacity of
100,000 automobiles. Its will manufacture the same 1997-model cars
that GM makes.
</P>
<P>
By the end of the first three years of operation, more than 80
percent of the car parts used by the joint venture will be made in
China, double the amount it will use when it begins production
next year.  
