<HEADLINE> Clan Fighting Kills Eight in Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Heavy clashes took place Friday
between the Marehan and Majerten clansmen outside the port town
of Kismaio, 500 km south of Mogadishu, in which eight people killed
and 15 others injured.
</P>
<P>
Reports from the field radios said, the fighting broke out
after the Majerten fighters launched an attack on the villages
formerly controlled by the Marehans and their allied militiamen
from the Habar Gidirs of Hussein Mohamed Aidid.
</P>
<P>
After a bitter fighting, the Majerten fighters took over the
two villages while the dislodged forces of Marehan clan retreated,
awaiting a chance to counterattack.
</P>
<P>
However, a militia commander from Hussein Aidid's forces has
denied that their aim is to capture the town of Kismaio, saying
their intention is to establish a strong defensive operation so
as to prevent further militia occupation in the territories under
their control by the Majerten clan.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 40 people have died and more than 75 others were
wounded since the armed clashes began between the Marehan
and Majerten militiamen over the control of port town of
Kismaio a week ago ago.
</P>
<P>
The Majerten militiamen are loyal to the son-in-law of
Somalia's late dictator General Mohamed, said Hirsi Morgan.
</P>
</TEXT>
