<HEADLINE> Dhaka, Tokyo to Initial Two Trade Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh and Japan are expected to
initial two agreements on bolstering economic ties between the two
countries during Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina's visit to Tokyo,
said Foreign Ministry officials.
</P>
<P>
Hasina will pay a six-day official visit to Japan from July 1.
</P>
<P>
A credit agreement providing 15 billion Japanese yen for three
infrastructure development projects in Bangladesh and an accord on
investment protection will be initialed during Hasina's Tokyo
visit, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Besides, Bangladesh is likely to seek Japanese financial
assistance for the construction of the proposed Ganges barrage. An
expenditure of 180 billion taka (about 4.18 billion U.S. dollars)
has been estimated for the construction of the barrage for storage
of the water.
</P>
<P>
Japan, the largest bilateral donor of Bangladesh, has been
extending financial support to a large number of big projects in
various sectors, including communications, health, rural
development, energy, industry, construction of cyclone centers and
social infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Hasina is scheduled to hold official talks
with Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto covering the entire
gamut of bilateral relations as well as regional and international
issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
There will also be a round-table conference with Japanese
business magnates and industrialists, and a seminar on investment.
</P>
