<HEADLINE> UNHCR to Hand Over to Tanzania Permanent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations High
Commissioner of Refugees (UNHCR ) branch in Tanzania, will hand
over to Tanzanian government the immovable structures it had
established for catering Rwandan refugees.
</P>
<P>
The 33 semi-permanent structures of about 8.3 million US
Dollars had been established by the UN agency in Karagwe District
to cater for Rwandese refugees. About 130,000 former Rwandan
refugees, who had stationed in the Karagwe District bordering
Rwanda, were repatriated last December.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman for UNHCR office in Tanzania, Vincent Kwesi
Parker said a few days ago that a formal handing over ceremony of
the immovable structures is scheduled for sometimes later this
month.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, primary schools for refugees at
Rubwera in Karagwe district are also in the package.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR, through the Save the Childrean Fund (SCF), it's
implementing partners in Karagwe, has constructed about 360
kilometers roads within the district.
</P>
<P>
The UN agency also financed the rehabilitation of the Kangwe
township and the Ngara airstrip. 
</P>
