<HEADLINE> Perec Drops out of European Cup Athletics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Double Olympic champion Marie-Jose
Perec of France has dropped out of the European Cup athletics
Meet, deciding not to join the French team in Munich on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Perec announced her decision in a statement after arriving
in Paris from California, where she trains.
</P>
<P>
The Olympic 200 and 400 meters champion said earlier that she
had decided against running in the 400 meters hurdles at the world
athletics championships in Athens in August to concentrate on the
400 meters flat.
</P>
<P>
She will appear in the 200 meters at a grand prix meeting in
Paris on Wednesday, the organisers said. 
</P>
