<HEADLINE> UN Envoy Confirmed Presence of Armed UNITA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- United Nations Special
Representative to Angola Blondin Beye confirmed here Friday that
a large amount of solidiers of the National Union for Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA) have not been disarmed.
</P>
<P>
Beye made the remarks at a press conference after
consultations with Angolan government and the UNITA delegation.
</P>
<P>
He said, the Joint Commission for Angolan Peace Process has
notified UNITA leaders to provide a namelist of the safety guards
for UNITA Chairman Jonas Savimbi and of policemen ocupying the
diomonds-rich areas so as to assemble and disband them
thereafter.
</P>
<P>
The joint commission was worried about the military operations
in the north and north-east of Angola, said the UN envoy, adding
that the military activities have put the peace process in a
dangerous position. 
</P>
