<HEADLINE> India Seeks Foreign Help in Salvaging Sunken </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 21 (Xinhua)-- India's Calcutta Port Trust (CPT)
has sought assistance from experts of Singapore and Hong Kong Port
authorities for salvaging the Korean vessel +MV Green Opal+ which
sank near Calcutta Port on Thursday, official sources said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The owner of the vessel had also been contacted to take
necessary steps to lift the wreck from the shipping channel to
ensure movement of ships from Calcutta Dock System.
</P>
<P>
The Korean vessel belonged to a Seoul-based management company,
and was carrying 9,000 tons of steel on its way to Kelong Port in
Singapore from India's Khidderpore Dock when the tragedy occurred.
All the 20 crew members, however, were rescued.  
</P>
