<HEADLINE> S. Korea to Buy More Advanced Weapons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The South Korean Defense Ministry
has finalized a military improvement program for this year to buy
more advanced weapons including submarine-attacking helicopters
and target-identifying radars.
</P>
<P>
The program, which is estimated to cost 225 million
U.S. dollars, includes the purchase of additional British Super
Lynx submarine-attacking Helicopters armed with air-to-ship missiles
and sonars, the Yonhap News Agency said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry initially acquired British sea battle helicopters
in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, the ministry will also purchase navy mines
from the United States and U.S.-made target-identifying radars to
be mounted on P3-C sea reconnaissance aircraft.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will also acquire armored personnel carriers armed
with 4.2-inch mortars for the marine corps and Russian-made
personnel carriers for the army. 
</P>
</TEXT>
