<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Light Up to Celebrate July I Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The decorative lights and neon
signs of Hong Kong's famous waterfront skyline will be illuminated
on the night of July 1 to celebrate Hong Kong's return to China,
the Better Hong Kong Foundation (BHKF) announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news conference, Chief Executive of the BHKF
Leonie Ki said this will be the biggest laser display in Hong
Kong's history in a dazzling segment of the "Hong Kong 97
Spectacular."
</P>
<P>
She said: "We appreciate your interest in the spectacular,
which will provide the people of Hong Kong with an indelible
memory of our first day of Hong Kong's return to China."
</P>
<P>
The spectacular is the largest ever to be produced entirely on
water, she said, adding that "City of Light -- the laser and light
show, one of five major segments in the spectacular, would pay
tribute to Hong Kong's dynamic cosmopolitan atmosphere and modern
technology."
</P>
<P>
Ki, also Executive Director of the spectacular, said the
spectacular is an hour-long program made up of five major segments
including "Pearl of the Orient," "Sea of Life," "City of Light,"
Unity" and "Celebration."
</P>
<P>
She said the BHKF had received commitments from over 80 percent
of the building owners on both shores of the Victoria Harbor to
participate in the planned July 1 show, noting that the
unforgettable impact will remind everyone of the vitality and
confidence the Hong Kong people have in their future.
</P>
<P>
At the same news conference, Matthew Joscelyne, production
coordinator of "City of Light," confirmed that "it will be the
biggest laser and light show that has ever been staged in Hong
Kong and will be a key element in the Hong Kong 97 Spectacular,
which is the largest show ever to be mounted on water."
</P>
<P>
"City of Light" will be one of the most striking effects of the
evening's program, he said, adding that "we will use six projects,
including two special multi-colored lasers in five locations on
both waterfronts and in the harbor itself, to project hundreds of
laser of laser beams of light," and "use almost 28
computer-controlled searchlights to dazzle viewers in 'City of
Light,' which has been choreographed to music specially written
for the occasion."
</P>
<P>
Joscelyne said the producers, Hong Kong's property industry,
New World Telephone and Hongkong Electric and China Light and
Power, have all worked together to design one of the largest
lighting special effects ever mounted anywhere in the world.
</P>
<P>
"They will be cued to dim out the outdoor lights and neon signs
in approximately 150 commercial buildings from the Macao Ferry
Terminal, to North point and the Tsim Sha Tsui waterfront, just
after the 'Hong Kong 97 Spectacular' begins at 21:00," he said.
</P>
<P>
After the "Sea of Life," an illuminated flotilla of decorated
barges, completes its parades around the harbor and the Karaoke
session -- "Million Singing With One Voice," the "City of Light"
sequence begins, according to Joscelyne. Lasers will burst out
from the "Pearl of the Orient" and radiate toward the darkened
city, he added.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters that symbolizing Hong Kong's return to the
motherland, the decorative signs and neon lights of the waterfront
buildings of this vibrant city will be dimmed out and switched on,
and the world will witness a vibrant and breathtaking city "come
alive and enter a new era."
</P>
<P>
This spectacular only is one of series of local people's
celebrations for Hong Kong's historical return to China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
