<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Maintains Good Public Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Current public security in Hong
Kong is good, with the crime rate plunging 16 percent in the first
five months of this year, local police said.
</P>
<P>
"Compared with other densely-populated cities, Hong Kong
remains one of the most secure places in the world," Commissioner
of Police Eddie Hui Ki-on told Xinhua in an exclusive interview.
</P>
<P>
He said that last year the overall number of crimes plummeted
by 14 percent from 1995 and the crime rate by 16.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
"There were only 1,253 crimes for every 100,000 people, the
lowest figure over the past 15 years," he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said, the police force achieved a case-solving
rate of 51.5 percent, one of the highest figures in the world.
</P>
<P>
At present, the Hong Kong society is stable and this has
created favorable conditions for the smooth return of Hong Kong to
the motherland," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
