<HEADLINE> Investments up by 15 Percent in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Investments in the Philippines went
up by 15 percent to 271.1 billion pesos (10.3 billion U.S.
dollars) in the first five months this year, Philippine News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Trade Undersecretary Melito Salazar as saying
the figure was the total amount approved by the country's Board of
Investments, the Philippine Economic Zone Authority, the Subic Bay
Metropolitan Authority and the Clark Development Corporation.
</P>
