were included in the total amount. Local economists estimated that
foreign direct investments declined due to the tumble of the
country's stock market in the second quarter of the year.
</P>
<P>
Salazar said the Board of Investments led all the agencies with
an investment of 6.7 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Subic and Clark, two economic zones turned from former U.S.
bases, also witnessed huge inflow of capital, with investments
reaching 240 million dollars and 51 million dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
Salazar said the improving investment is an indication the
country is attracting much-needed capital to finance industrial
development and enhance the sustained economic growth. 
