<HEADLINE> Beijing Cracks Down on Sale of Non-Iodine Salt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has banned the sale of
table salt in farm produce markets as of June 20 and listed 24
monopolized enterprises for wholesale of iodine salt.
</P>
<P>
The move is aimed at cracking down on the illegal trading of
non-iodine salt in peasant markets and imposing a stricter control
of the salt sale.
</P>
<P>
The listed enterprises include Beijing Salt Corporation and
Haidian Supply and Marketing Cooperative.
</P>
<P>
The municipal commission of commerce and industry and commerce
administration department will check up on the salt sale and
punish those who violate the regulation.
</P>
<P>
China has decided to eliminate iodine-deficiency disease by
the end of this century. The most convenient and cheap way to
prevent the disease is to take iodine salt every day.  
</P>
</TEXT>
