<HEADLINE> AIDS Orphans On Rise in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- At least 70,000 children are
orphaned by HIV/AIDS every year in Zambia and the number is
expected to reach 600,000 in the country by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by Community Development Minister Newstead
Zimba, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Zimba said the number of children earning a living off the
streets in the country is on the rise due to poverty, broken
homes, and breadwinners dying of AIDS.
</P>
<P>
Aids is a popular disease in Zambia. The authorities concerned
have launched drives to raise the people's awareness of its
danger to be prevented from its infection. 
</P>
