<HEADLINE> S. Zambia Farmers Urged to Fight Grain Pests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- All stakeholders in Zambia
including the private sector and the environmental council of
Zambia are urged to involve actively in fighting against the
larger grain borer in the Southern Province of the country.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was made by Songowayo Zyambo, Chairman of the
Larger Grain Borer National Steering Committee and National
Co-ordinator of the Zambia National Farmers Union (ZNFU) in an
interview today with the local press.
</P>
<P>
Zyambo called for the establishment of a network to help
distribute a chemical named Acetellic Super to the small scale
farmers who are most affected by the borer attacks.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that the ZNFU has been distributing the chemical,
adding with an appeal to other institutions to help in
distributing Acetellic Super which also works on other pests
before a maize crisis befalls the nation.
</P>
<P>
The larger grain borer attacks maize in storage by turning it
into powder. The pest has been found in a number of districts in
the southern province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
