<HEADLINE> Colin McRae Set on Victory in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) - Former world rally champion Colin
McRae set off from Beijing early Saturday as hot favourite to win
the inaugural three-day China Rally.
</P>
<P>
China saw its first FIA-sanctioned, cloverleaf style rally
shooting off at 7:50 a.m., with 32 crews including drivers from
Britain, Japan, Sweden, Austria, Malaysia, New Zealand and China.
</P>
<P>
The main challenge to 1995 world champion McRae is expected to
come from his Subaru team-mate, Kenneth Eriksson of Sweden.
</P>
<P>
The first of the 21 special stages started in Huairou county,
some 60 kilomters north of Beijing, and comprises 363 kilometers
of the total 1,458 kilomter route.
</P>
<P>
Around 10,000 spectators turned out Friday evening to give the
drivers a ceremonial send-off -- complete with lion dancers,
fireworks and sky-divers. 
</P>
