played an increasingly active role in promoting exchanges among
young people in the inland areas and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Since 1990, the federation has received over 500 young visitors
from Hong Kong and sent over 150 people to the metropolis for the
exchange in various fields.
</P>
<P>
These were stated by Bayinqolu, Executive Vice-Chairman of the
federation, in a recent interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
This year, the organization has attached much importance to the
upcoming return of Hong Kong and has sponsored many activities to
help inland youth learn about the history and present situation of
Hong Kong as well as the knowledge on the Basic Law of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, other activities such as tree-planting and
charity-donation were held for the purpose, according to Bayinqolu.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the federation will carry out exchanges with
youth groups in Hong Kong based on the concept of "one country,
two systems" and the principles of non-subordination,
non-interference and mutual respect. 
