<HEADLINE> Exhibition Hall For Classical Buildings In Nanjing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition hall to display the
architectural developments of China 1,400 years ago has been set
up in this capital city of east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition hall is built in the style of a residential
courtyard on Wuyi Lane, where Wang Dao and Xie An, two famous
senior officials of the Eastern Jin Dynasty (317-420) built
significant houses.
</P>
<P>
Pictures, paintings, and historical relics are on display to
help visitors get a sense of the architecture, culture, history,
and social development of the period.
</P>
<P>
Nanjing was the capital of the Six Dynasties (222-589).
</P>
