<HEADLINE> HK's Tourism Continues to Grow: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's tourism industry has
witnessed a phenomenal growth over the past 40 years, said Donald
Tsang, financial secretary.
</P>
<P>
At Hong Kong Tourist Association's 40 Years of Wonders -- Time
Capsule Launching Ceremony held here today, he said, "Apart from
being one of the most popular and competitive cities in the world
for doing business, Hong Kong is now the most popular tourist
destination in the region and one of the most popular tourist
destinations in the world."
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong ranks 8th world-wide in terms of total tourism
receipts and tourism is now the biggest foreign exchange earner
among its services industry, he said.
</P>
<P>
For this year, Hong Kong expects the number of overseas
visitors to surge to a record high of over 12 million, which is
about twice the size of Hong Kong's population, he said.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that these visitors will spend as much as 95
billion HK dollars (about 12.2 billion U.S. dollars) in shopping,
hotel accommodation and entertainment, he added.
</P>
<P>
The commissioning of the new airport at Chek Lap Kok next year
will remove the capacity constraints of travelers by air and give
a great boost to the industry, he said.
</P>
<P>
"I am confident that Hong Kong would have seen at least another
period of robust growth in tourism, and Hong Kong will continue to
be a place where "Wonders Never Cease". 
</P>
