<HEADLINE> 2.5 Kilograms of Heroin Detected in Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 21 (Xinhua) -- About 2.5 kilograms of heroin
along with four suspects and a boat were detected Friday by Sri
Lankan police at near coast of Colombo, according to police
sources here today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the drug worth about 855,000 U.S. dollars was
smuggled from India. The four persons, two men and two women, are
alleged to be linked to this smuggling ring.
</P>
<P>
The leader of the smuggling ring, a rich businessman, has gone
missing since the detection, said the sources, adding that the
police searched his house and other possible hiding places without
any success.  
</P>
</TEXT>
