<DOCNO> XIE19970621.0148 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "One Country, Two Systems" Policy is Wise: Russian Diplomat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The policy of "one country, two
systems," "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" and "a high
degree of autonomy" formulated by Chinese leaders is a wise one,
according to a senior Russian diplomat.
</P>
<P>
In his office in the Sun Hung Kai Center building near the
Victoria Harbor, Consul-General Kirill Ivanov told Xinhua that
this policy constitutes an important guarantee for maintaining
prosperity of Hong Kong after its return to China.
</P>
<P>
"Maintaining a stable and prosperous Hong Kong is not only in
the interest of China, but also conducive to the stability and
development of the Asia-Pacific region and the world as a whole,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that after its return to China, Hong
Kong will play the role as a bridge in Russian-Chinese economic
and trade relations.
</P>
<P>
He said that Russia is ready to continue to increase its
"presence" in Hong Kong and use Hong Kong as a "bridge" for
promoting economic and trade cooperation with China's inland areas
and other countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Consulate-General in Hong Kong was opened in 1994.
Ivanov came here in July 1994 as the first post-Soviet
consul-general. His previous posts were all in Asia, working in
Beijing in the 1960s, and in Singapore and Malaysia in the
following decade.
</P>
<P>
One of his first official activities was to preside over the
establishment of the Russian Trade Association in Hong Kong, which
is dedicated to developing Hong Kong-Russian ties in trade and
investment.
</P>
<P>
He said, "The establishment of the Russian Consulate-General
demonstrates our confidence in Hong Kong's stability and
prosperity after its return to China, as well as in the role Hong
Kong will play in the future."
</P>
<P>
In the past three year, he said, Russian-Hong Kong trade volume
has increased three times, surging from about 400 million U.S.
dollars in 1994 to more than 1.2 billion U.S. dollars in 1996.
More and more Russian artists, musicians and sportsmen come to
visit Hong Kong, while an increasing number of Hong Kong people
travel to Russia for business and tourism.
</P>
<P>
He said that Russia has always regarded Hong Kong as an
international financial, trade, shipping, tourism and information
center.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Consulate-General serves to promote economic and
trade ties between Russia and Hong Kong, and between Russia and
China and the whole of the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
Russia is rich in natural resources, has advanced technology
and is a market with enormous potential, he said, adding that Hong
Kong has sufficient funds, a flexible production capacity and rich
managerial expertise.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the Hong Kong business community
will invest in Russia's resource-rich Siberia and Far East region.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the Russian and Chinese leaders have decided
to forge a strategic cooperation partnership oriented with the
21st century.
</P>
<P>
The two countries enjoy enormous potential in economic, trade
and technological cooperation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Russia has been carrying out large-scale economic and trade
cooperation with the northern part of China, but has not done so
with developed provinces in south China.
</P>
<P>
With its special geographic location and unique advantages,
Hong Kong can play the role as a bridge in economic and trade
cooperation between Russia and various provinces in south China,
he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that cooperation will be very fruitful if China's
inland areas provide land and labor, Russia supplies raw materials
and technology, and Hong Kong provides funds and managerial
expertise. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
