<HEADLINE> Myanmar Wants to Set up Advanced Wood-Based Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Local entrepreneurs should form
partnerships with foreign counterparts to set up advanced
wood-based enterprises to boost wood-based value-added exports,
the New Light of Myanmar today quoted a senior government official
as saying.
</P>
<P>
At an inspection tour to wood-based factories on Friday,
Myanmar Minister for Forestry Lieutenant-General Chit Swe said
that extended production of wood-based, value-added goods in
Myanmar will lead to termination of log exports, especially teak.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar is the main teak log exporter in the world.
</P>
<P>
The minister stressed the need to strive to set up furniture
and value-added goods enterprises to manufacture more
international class furniture and value-added goods.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar private companies have exported various types of
parquet, door frames and furniture to Spain, Japan, Singapore,
Thailand, the Republic of Korea and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest official data, the export of forest
products in the 1996-97 fiscal year increased to about 212.7
million US dollars, representing 24.4 percent of the country's
total export, as compared with over 188 million dollars,
representing 19 percent of the total export in the previous year.
 
</P>
