<HEADLINE> hkhk - HK Provisional Legislature Holds 12th Meeting in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The Provisional Legislative
Council (PLC) of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) held its 12th plenary meeting this morning in Shenzhen, a
city in southern China.
</P>
<P>
This is believed to be the last plenary meeting for the
law-making body before July 1, 1997 when Hong Kong returns to
China.
</P>
<P>
At the beginning of today's meeting, Secretary of Justice Leung
Oi-sie presented to the PLC a consultation document entitled
"Introduction to Hong Kong Reunification Bill 1997".
</P>
<P>
The Reunification Bill, to be gazetted and passed through three
readings in the small hours of July 1, is an arrangement made to
ratify all bills passed by the PLC before June 30 and to deal with
various transition-related matters.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the interim body will resume the second reading
debate on four bills later today, namely, the Hong Kong Court of
Final Appeal (Amendment) Bill 1997, the Judicial Service
Commission (Amendment) Bill 1997, the Immigration (Amendment)
(No.3) Bill 1997 and the Oaths and Declarations (Amendment) Bill
1997.
</P>
<P>
The four bills are expected to pass the third reading today,
adding to 13 the total number of bills endorsed by the provisional
legislature before June 30, 1997.
</P>
<P>
A subcommittee on the consultation paper on the Reunification
Bill will hold its first meeting after the PLC's plenary meeting,
and then submit a verbal report to the House Committee, which will
hold its 10th meeting here today and tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
The House Committee will also discuss the logistical
arrangements for the PLC meeting in the early hours of July 1 and
the orientation seminar on July 3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
