<HEADLINE> Registration of Voters Continues in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Filipinos who failed to register
last weekend for the 1998 national elections are coming to their
precincts today and tomorrow to list as qualified voters.
</P>
<P>
According to the Commission on Elections, only 25 percent of
the 40 million qualified voters registered on June 14 and 15, the
first two days of a four-day registration of voters.
</P>
<P>
The low turnout stemmed from the commission's failure to inform
the voters of what identification documents they should bring,
local media reported.
</P>
<P>
The remaining 30 million should register today and tomorrow,
the Commission on Elections said.
</P>
<P>
The country will have its presidential, parliamentary and local
elections in May next year. President Fidel Ramos has repeated
that he would step down in 1998.  
</P>
