<HEADLINE> News In Brief On Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Following are news in brief on
local activities to celebrate the upcoming return of Hong Kong to
the motherland:

-- 10 Days Ahead
</P>
<P>
Early this morning, thousands of people from Beijing and other
parts of the country gathered in front of the countdown clock
erected at Tian'anmen Square to mark 10 days remaining until China
resumes the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on July 1.
</P>
<P>
Since May, the Chinese capital has become a sea of dancers and
singers every day as over three million local people have held art
festivals of various kinds to greet the return of Hong Kong.

-- Gala At Tomb of Chinese Ancestor
</P>
<P>
On Friday, a grand performance was held on the square of the
Tomb of Huangdi, who is seen as one of the ancestors for the
Chinese nation, to celebrate the forthcoming return of Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
The tomb is located in Huangling County, Shaanxi Province in
the northwest and is a major site in the country to show people's
national and patriotic compassion.

-- Poem-Reciting Gathering
</P>
<P>
Latest works of local poets in Shanghai Metropolis were
recently presented at a local theater which was broadcast live to
over 100 million tv watchers in East China.
</P>
<P>
The poets read aloud to express their deep feeling for the
late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping and their happiness about the
upcoming return of Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
