<HEADLINE> Mexico Earns $758 mln From Coffee Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Mexican coffee exports earned
758.106 million U.S. dollars between the October, 1996 to May,
1997, season, 14 percent higher than that of the whole previous
period, according to the Mexican Coffee Institute.
</P>
<P>
Coffee exports earned 663.842 million dollars during the
1995-1996 season, said the institute in a report published today.
</P>
<P>
By volume, the exports of the first eight months represented
86.78 percent of the previous total and amounted to 3.973 million
60-kilo bags, compared to the 4.578 million bags of the 1995-1996
season.
</P>
<P>
The report said prices registered a rising trend from January
to May, which had a positive influence on the income.
</P>
<P>
The average international price was 128.11 dollars for 100
pounds in January, and in May it reached 260.76 dollars, which was
a record for the past 10 years.
</P>
<P>
Mexico ranks fourth in the world in coffee production after
Brazil, Colombia and Indonesia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
