<HEADLINE> German Wins Fourth Stage at Tour of Switzerland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Jan Ullrich of Germany took the
fourth stage of the Tour of Switzerland cycling race on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Ullrich, runner-up in the French classic last year, won the
183.2-kilometer fourth stage from La Chaux-de-Fonds to Kandersteg
in a time of 4 hours 26 minutes 23 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Ullrich left his five breakaway partners behind five kilometers
from the finish on the gruelling final climb into Kandersteg high
in the Swiss Alps, beating Italy's Stefano Garzelli and
Switzerland's Roland Meier by 38 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Italy's Michele Bartoli, winner of Liege-Bastogne-Liege
classic, was fourth with one minute 8 seconds behind.
</P>
<P>
Christophe Agnolutto of France retained a comfortable advantage
of two minutes 24 seconds at the top of the overall rankings ahead
of Italy's Valentino Fois. 
</P>
</TEXT>
