<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Wimbledon star Jana Novotna was
facing the prospect of six matches in two days on the eve of
Wimbledon as rain forced the pre-Wimbldon WTA event into extra
time on Friday.
</P>
<P>
After rain for the second day running, a Sunday finish is now
planned provided progress can be made with the quarter-finals and
two semi-finals on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
If not, the organizers said they are ready to ditch the 278,000
pound (about 430,000 dollars) event rather than take it indoors at
the nearby David Lloyd Tennis Centre.
</P>
<P>
Czech Republic ace Novotna was just three points from the
semi-final when the rain returned as she led Japan's Ai Sugiyami
6-2, 6-5.
</P>
<P>
Now the 1993 Wimbledon singles finalist must pick up the action
again in search of a last-four clash with either Nathalie Tauziat
or Natasha Zvereva.
</P>
<P>
But she is also involved in the doubles as one half of the
second-seeded team with American Mary Joe Fernandez and they have
also only reached the quarter-finals of that event.
</P>
<P>
The singles top seed and title holder Monica Seles, trailing
5-7, 2-2 to Holland's Brenda Schultz-McCarthy, hopes to retrieve
that deficit and set up a clash with either Arantxa Sanchez
Vicario of Spain or Romania's Irina Spirlea. 
