<HEADLINE> Public Transportation Lanes to be Used in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Drivers are warned to observe
regulations on the use of new public transportation lanes along
Chang'an Avenue in the Chinese capital which will be put into use
on June 25, according to Beijing's traffic authorities.
</P>
<P>
Drivers who violate the regulations by driving vehicles in the
special lanes at prohibited times will be severely punished, said
Yu Chunquan, vice-director of the Beijing Municipal Public
Security Traffic Administration Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The drivers' work enterprises will also be punished, Yu said at
a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Starting next Wednesday, the far-right lanes for motor
vehicles in both directions from Dawang Bridge through Dongdan
Crossroad and Xidan Crossroad to Xinxing Bridge will be designated
as special lanes for public transportation between 6 am and 8 pm
every day.
</P>
<P>
Only buses, trolley buses and mini-buses allowed to operate by
traffic-administration departments can use the special lanes and
all other motor vehicles can not drive or park in such lanes
between the specified time periods, Yu said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
