<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US, EU Initial Agreements on Transatlantic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Denver, Colorado, June 20 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. and the European
Union initialed here today some landmark agreements that represent
a new level of transatlantic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The accords will reduce trade barriers, increase U.S. exports
and promote more efficient regulation in sectors that account for
approximately 50 billion U.S. dollars in two-way trade between the
U.S. and the EU, according to a press release by the office of
Press Secretary of the White House.
</P>
<P>
The Mutual recongnition Agreements will eliminate the need for
duplicative testing, inspection, or certification of products
destined for trade on each side of the Antlantic, while protecting
the health and safty of consumers on both sides of the ocean.
</P>
<P>
The sectors covered under the agreements include
telecommuncations equipment, information technology, medical
devices and pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
The package, when implemented, will serve to increase U.S.
exports by saving manufacturers up to 10 percent of the cost of
delivering U.S. exports to Europe and to enhance transatlantic
cooperation to protect the health and safty of the two peoples.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
