<HEADLINE> Cuba, Colombia Sign Sports Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Cuba and Colombia signed today a
sports agreement in this city to expand their collaboration in
sports and strengthen their bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by the presidents of the Olympic
Committees: Andres Botero, of Colombia, and Jose Ramon Fernandez,
of Cuba.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will help raise the technical level in the
organization of programs, counseling for the formation and
improvement of specialists and trainers, as well as in management,
infrastructure, and sports medicine and informations.
</P>
<P>
Fernandez stressed that Cubans and Colombians will cooperate in
the improvement of the relations of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Colombia, with a population of 40 million, is a country with a
big sports potentiality, and to realize it needs to increase the
number of Cuban techincians, now some 80, in the South American
country, said Fernandez.
</P>
<P>
Botero thanked the attentions received during his visit to the
island and confirmed the intentions of his country to be a sports
power in the next millennium, because it wants the city of
Medellin to be the host of the 2003 Panamerican Games. 
