<HEADLINE> Talks on East Timor End With Constructive Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 20 (Xinhua) -- The two-day talks on East
Timor, held by U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan with the
ministers for foreign affairs of Indonesia and Portugal, Ali
Alatas and Jaime Gama, concluded today with constructive results.
</P>
<P>
A statement by the spokesman's office said the discussions were
intensive, frank and constructive with two decisions reached:
</P>
<P>
1. The discussions will continue at the working level chaired
by the personal representative of the secretary-general for East
Timor, Jamsheed Marker. The first meeting will start on June 28,
1997. Both sides have agreed that the discussions will be kept
confidential.
</P>
<P>
2. The All-inclusive Intra-East Timorese Dialogue will
continue. Every effort will be made to hold the next meeting in
August 1997. The personal representative of the secretary-general
will carry out the necessary preparatory consultations for this
purpose.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, the secretary-general expressed his thanks
to the two ministers for their presence and for the constructive
and cooperative spirit in which the discussions were conducted.
</P>
</TEXT>
