<HEADLINE> Dow Sets New Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street had a most active
session today, with more indexes edging into record territories.
</P>
<P>
The Dow rose 19.45 points to 7,796.51, surrendering most of
the 57-point gains in the earlier session.
</P>
<P>
Decliners outnumbered advancers by 4 to 3 on the New York Stock
Exchange, with the volume totaling 652.73 million shares as
against 536.90 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 0.71 to 898.70, and
the NYSE's composite index rose 0.08 to 467.84, both setting new
records.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 0.46 to a record high of
1,447.60, but the American Stock Exchange composite index fell
5.03 to 623.27.
</P>
<P>
Stocks also benefited from strength in bonds. The yield on the
30-year Treasury bond, which moves in the opposite direction from
the price, fell to 6.64 percent late today from 6.67 percent late
Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
