<HEADLINE> Bosnian Parliament Adopts Economic Laws </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, June 20 (Xinhua) -- The parliament of
Bosnia-Herzegovina today adopted a package of economic laws
required by the international community for convening an
international conference on the country's reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
The seven laws in the so-called "quick start package," which
deals such issues as customs policy, central bank and foreign
trade, are the first legislation approved by the two chambers of
parliament -- the houses of peoples and representatives since
they were elected last September.
</P>
<P>
Despite the adoption of the laws, the donors conference
originally scheduled on June 24 an 25 has been postponed, said the
the World Bank and the European Commission which organized the
conference.
</P>
<P>
The organizers said that the conference will not be rescheduled
until the country reaches an agreement with the International
Monetary Fund. 
</P>
